    fix: ddx update/install check GitHub for actual latest version

    - ddx update now fetches the real latest release from each package's
      GitHub repo instead of comparing against the hardcoded registry version.
      Supports --force to reinstall even if already at latest.
      Always invalidates the DDx binary update cache so the next run
      re-checks upstream regardless of the 24h TTL.

    - ddx install helix now fetches the latest GitHub release tag before
      comparing, so "already up to date" reflects the actual upstream state.

    - update.FetchLatestReleaseForRepo(repoURL) added for arbitrary repos.
    - update.InvalidateCache() added to reset the binary update check cache.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

